review 1: Baki Rice fields , picturesque view of terrain farming at Ubud in Bali . So much of lush greenery worth taking a long trip of two plus hours from the central of the city.
review 2: Sunset view villa with 4 spacious bedroom equiped with flat screen tv, hot shower, large infinity swimming pool. Great for party and reunion, and also breakfast served daily, more info and Reservation +6285103771369
review 3: It's adventurous, green, beautiful and different. For adrenaline rush do try Bali swing.

name: Bebek Uma Sari Resto
address: Jl. Raya Singapadu No.10, Singapadu Kaler, Kec. Sukawati, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80571, Indonesia
review 1: We had lunch at Bebek Uma Sari Resto. The restaurant is nicely decorated and well designed. There are normal seatings as well as  individual huts on the water which looks great. Yes they can speak English and no issues with ordering foods. The service is quick and effective. Food was prepared within short time and delicious. They have onsite toilets facilities. It is a good place for family lunch. Overall we are very happy with our visit.
review 2: Tried the mixed satay here and it was delicious. They are happy to replace one meat with another for the satay. Loved the ambience and my family tried other dishes here and they were very happy. Service was quick too. Prices are slightly on the higher side.
review 3:
Cozy and lovely place, good prices to
U can get table above fish pond so u have fishes under you really cool
review 4: 10/10 for this beautiful location, it was so calming and special. Very nice people and good food. Would always go there again.
review 5: Seat relaxed at Saung with ponds below, and feet space well prepared. The food is delicious especially the traditional vegetables  of the young banana tree cooked in Balinese taste aka Jukut Ares served with fried duck and urab (mixed steam vegetables with grated coconut). Drink young coconut.

name: Warung Tepi Tebing
address: Jl. Raya Singapadu, Singapadu Kaler, Kec. Sukawati, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80571, Indonesia
review 1: We stopped in here after an ATV tour next door, and it was the best meal we had in Bali! The food was delicious (especially the Ayam Betutu), the service was excellent and the whole place is beautiful, set around fish ponds with table in little individual thatched pods around the edge. Such good value too.
review 2: A lovely quiet restaurant which is not overrated or overly crowded. The food was lovely. The best thing was their sambal. They serve 3 types of sambal with the bebek goreng and fried fish (most of the main dishes). The tempeh & tauhu tempura was just lovely! The staff were friendly too. Enjoyed our lunch here. Beautifully landscaped. Take the time to walk around the compound!
review 3: Food was terrible and horrible, all menus what we ordered were frozen stuffs. Also the price is quite expensive. Recommend not to order pizza or fish and chips..
review 4:
The food was alright, I found it to be a bit overpriced. The dishes we ordered were decent, but nothing stood out as especially delicious. The atmosphere was nice, with a lovely view of the river, and the service was friendly.

However, given the somewhat high price point, I would have expected the food to be a bit more impressive.

I'd say Warung Tepi Tebing is an okay choice if you're in the area and looking for a place to eat, but be prepared to spend a bit more than you might expect.
review 5:
This place has a very nice view of the river and camping style of dining. You definitely feel relaxed here. The food is ok, not particularly better than any other Warung, considering the price is obviously on the expensive side.

We went there because our driver recommended this place.

review 1:
Not far from Ubud central (approx 15 mins).
Clean and homey place! Loved it here. Would recommend this place to anyone that needs a roomüôåüèª
review 2: That's a place where you can stay when you want to feel like home. It's quiet, close to Ubud center , like 10 minutes with scooter and from here if you have a scooter you can go everywhere on Bali. This can be your basecamp for a long-term stay. review 3: so comfortable for long stay. Large room with seperate living room, main kitchen access, public pool. Close to Ubud

name: Ubud Corner 88
address: Br. Mawang Kaja no. 88 Desa Lodtunduh, Lodtunduh, Kecamatan Ubud, Ubud-Gianyar, Bali 80571, Indonesia
review 1: I loved it. The yoga teachers were so good and pleasant.  The staf were so wonderful and helpful. Rooms were clean and comfortable. Highly recommended. Met so many wonderful people from all over the world and such good vibes.
review 2:
Great villa for yoga retreat! The workers here are super nice and attentive. I really loves the vibes here. Doing my YTT here and it‚Äôs really rejuvenating to be able to stay here in the middle of the forest.
Please be minded no alcohol/drugs onsite and we do vegan meals here.
review 3:
I stayed her 5 days for a yoga retreat. The service was excellent, the food was delicious, the room was very clean and the bed was comfy. The private pool was great and had a nice view :).

The yoga/meditation retreat was fabulous, a great experience that I will remember. If you want to relax, recenter and embark on a spiritual journey, this is the place for you!
review 4: Does it get more perfect than this? I came for a yoga retreat (Blooming Lotus) and this property just blew me away. The service is impeccable, the food is phenomenal (and I‚Äôm no vegan) and the view‚Ä¶it‚Äôs paradise. One of the most gorgeous places and best hotel experiences I‚Äôve ever had.
review 5: Ubud Corner 88 is incredible - beautiful villas and pools, very clean, the staff are friendly and helpful, the views are amazing and of course the layout is great for a daily yoga/ meditation practice. Oh and I highly recommend the good karma massage!
